Rating: 4
Delicious and easy to make. I've made it twice, substituting fish stock for the clam juice. I also threw in a bay leaf and fresh herbs from the garden. The second time I made it, I used onion, chives, and garlic instead of the scallions. I also used leftover cooked corn on the cob. I imagine you could substitute frozen corn if your in a hurry, but I think the fresh really made a difference. (Sorry if this appears twice. When I hit edit from the preview button, put me in the reviews page and so I don't know if the first entry stuck or got lost in cyberspace.)

